Details.Textbox7: New Test- Our aim is to disseminate information on OSH related good practices, develop safety culture and highlight importance of co-operation in all levels. Our activities are agreed on and executed together with the national social partners and expert organisations. The Department for Work and gender equality at the Ministry of Social Affairs and Health is acting as national Focal Point in Finland. The Department for Work and Gender Equality steers the supervision and administration of occupational safety and health, prepares and develops legislation and policies on occupational safety and health and conducts international cooperation in the field of occupational safety and health.In addition, the Department prepares and develops the Government’s gender equality policy and gender equality legislation and promotes equality between the genders.
